<!--
  Info.plist additions for SiteSync PM iOS shell.

  After running `npx cap add ios`, paste these <key>/<string> pairs
  into ios/App/App/Info.plist before the closing </dict>. Capacitor's
  generated Info.plist already has UIRequiredDeviceCapabilities,
  UISupportedInterfaceOrientations, etc. — only add the items below.

  Apple rejects apps that use a permission-protected API without a
  matching Usage Description string. Each string must be specific and
  describe the user-facing benefit, not the technical mechanism.
  ("To take photos for your daily log" — yes. "Required by camera API" — no.)
-->

<!-- @capacitor/camera : photo capture for daily logs, punch lists, RFIs -->
<key>NSCameraUsageDescription</key>
<string>SiteSync uses your camera to capture jobsite photos for daily logs, punch list items, and RFIs.</string>

<!-- @capacitor/camera : reading existing photos when user picks from library -->
<key>NSPhotoLibraryUsageDescription</key>
<string>SiteSync lets you attach existing photos from your library to project records.</string>

<!-- @capacitor/camera : saving captured photos back to the library -->
<key>NSPhotoLibraryAddUsageDescription</key>
<string>SiteSync can save jobsite photos you take in the app to your photo library.</string>

<!-- @capacitor/geolocation : tagging field captures with GPS for site verification -->
<key>NSLocationWhenInUseUsageDescription</key>
<string>SiteSync tags jobsite photos and daily logs with your location so the office can verify which site an entry came from.</string>

<!-- Voice memos on field captures (if enabled in v1; remove if not) -->
<key>NSMicrophoneUsageDescription</key>
<string>SiteSync records short voice notes you can attach to daily logs and field captures.</string>

<!--
  ATS exception: Capacitor's WKWebView talks to https://*.supabase.co,
  https://*.sentry.io, https://*.posthog.com, https://*.liveblocks.io,
  and https://api.openweathermap.org. All are HTTPS with valid certs,
  so no NSAppTransportSecurity exception is required. DO NOT add
  NSAllowsArbitraryLoads — Apple will reject for "broader than needed."
-->

<!--
  Push notifications: handled by capability + entitlement, not Info.plist.
  In Xcode: Signing & Capabilities → + Capability → Push Notifications.
-->

<!--
  Background modes (if push wakes the app to fetch data):
  In Xcode: Signing & Capabilities → + Capability → Background Modes →
  check "Remote notifications". This adds UIBackgroundModes to Info.plist.
-->

<!--
  Encryption export compliance — set this to avoid the question
  on every TestFlight build. SiteSync uses only standard HTTPS/TLS
  via the OS, which is exempt under U.S. EAR §740.17(b)(1).
-->
<key>ITSAppUsesNonExemptEncryption</key>
<false/>
